{{pp-move-indef}}
{{May calendar|float=right}}
{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[1194]] &amp;ndash; King [[Richard I of England]] gives [[Portsmouth]] its first [[Royal Charter]].
*[[1230]] &amp;ndash; [[William de Braose (died 1230)|William de Braose]] is hanged by Prince [[Llywelyn the Great]].
*[[1335]] &amp;ndash; [[Otto, Duke of Austria|Otto the Merry]], Duke of [[Austria]], becomes [[Carinthia (duchy)|Duke of Carinthia]].
*[[1536]] &amp;ndash; [[Anne Boleyn]], [[Queen consort|Queen of England]], is arrested and imprisoned on charges of [[adultery]], [[incest]], [[treason]] and [[witchcraft]].
*[[1559]] &amp;ndash; [[John Knox]] returns from exile to [[Scotland]] to become the leader of the beginning [[Scottish Reformation]].
*[[1568]] &amp;ndash; [[Mary, Queen of Scots]], escapes from [[Loch Leven Castle]].
*[[1611]] &amp;ndash; [[King James Bible]] is published for the first time in London, England, by printer Robert Barker.
*[[1670]] &amp;ndash; King [[Charles II of England]] grants a permanent charter to the [[Hudson's Bay Company]] to open up the [[fur trade]] in [[North America]].
*[[1672]] &amp;ndash; [[John Maitland, Duke of Lauderdale|John Maitland]] becomes [[Duke of Lauderdale]] and [[Earl of March]].
*[[1808]] &amp;ndash; Outbreak of the [[Peninsular War]]: The people of [[Madrid]] [[Dos de Mayo Uprising|rise up in rebellion]] against [[France|French]] occupation. [[Francisco de Goya]] later memorializes this event in his painting [[The Second of May 1808]].
*[[1816]] &amp;ndash; Marriage of [[Leopold I of Belgium|Léopold of Saxe-Coburg]] and [[Princess Charlotte Augusta of Wales|Charlotte Augusta]].
*[[1829]] &amp;ndash; After anchoring nearby, Captain [[Charles Fremantle]] of the [[HMS Challenger|HMS ''Challenger'']], declares the [[Swan River Colony]] in [[Australia]].
*[[1863]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Stonewall Jackson]] is wounded by friendly fire while returning to camp after reconnoitering during the [[Battle of Chancellorsville]]. He succumbs to [[pneumonia]] eight days later.
*[[1866]] &amp;ndash; [[Peru]]vian defenders fight off [[Spain|Spanish]] fleet at the [[Battle of Callao]].
*[[1876]] &amp;ndash; The [[April Uprising]] breaks out in [[Bulgaria]].
*[[1879]] &amp;ndash; The [[Spanish Socialist Worker's Party]] is founded in Casa Labra Pub (city of Madrid) by the historical Spanish workers' leader [[Pablo Iglesias]].
*[[1885]] &amp;ndash; ''[[Good Housekeeping]]'' magazine goes on sale for the first time.
*  1885   &amp;ndash; [[Cree]] and [[Assiniboine people|Assiniboine]] warriors win the [[Battle of Cut Knife]], their largest victory over [[Canada|Canadian]] forces during the [[North-West Rebellion]].
*  1885   &amp;ndash; The [[Congo Free State]] is established by King [[Léopold II of Belgium]].
*[[1889]] &amp;ndash; [[Menelik II of Ethiopia|Menelik II]], Emperor of [[Ethiopia]], signs a treaty of amity with [[Italy]], which gives Italy control over [[Eritrea]].
*[[1906]] &amp;ndash; Closing ceremony of the [[1906 Intercalated Games|Intercalated Games]] in [[Athens]], [[Greece]].
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[General Motors Corporation|General Motors]] acquires the [[Chevrolet Motor Company]] of [[Delaware]].
*[[1920]] &amp;ndash; The first game of the [[Negro National League (the first)|Negro National League baseball]] is played in [[Indianapolis, Indiana]].
*[[1932]] &amp;ndash; Comedian [[Jack Benny]]'s radio show airs for the first time.
*[[1933]] &amp;ndash; ''[[Gleichschaltung]]'': [[Adolf Hitler]] bans [[trade union]]s.
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; Following the [[1941 Iraqi coup d'état|coup d'état]] against [[Iraq]] Crown Prince [['Abd al-Ilah]] earlier that year, the [[United Kingdom]] launches the [[Anglo-Iraqi War]] to restore him to power.
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Fall of Berlin]]: The [[Soviet Union]] announces the capture of [[Berlin]] and Soviet soldiers hoist their red flag over the [[Reichstag (building)|''Reichstag'' building]].
*  1945   &amp;ndash; World War II: [[Italian Campaign (World War II)|Italian Campaign]] &amp;ndash; General [[Heinrich von Vietinghoff]] signs the official instrument of surrender of all [[Wehrmacht]] forces in Italy.
*  1945   &amp;ndash; World War II: The US 82nd Airborne Division liberates [[Wöbbelin concentration camp]] finding 1000 dead inmates, most starved to death.
*[[1946]] &amp;ndash; The &quot;[[Battle of Alcatraz]]&quot; takes place, killing two guards and three inmates.
*[[1952]] &amp;ndash; The world's first ever [[jet airliner]], the [[De Havilland Comet]] 1 makes its maiden flight, from [[London]] to [[Johannesburg]].
*[[1955]] &amp;ndash; [[Tennessee Williams]] wins the [[Pulitzer Prize for Drama]] for ''[[Cat on a Hot Tin Roof]]''.
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; [[Berthold Seliger]] launches a rocket with three stages and a maximum flight altitude of more than 100 kilometres near [[Cuxhaven]]. It is the only [[sounding rocket]] developed in [[Germany]].
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: An explosion sinks the [[USS Card (CVE-11)|USS ''Card'']] while docked at [[Ho Chi Minh City|Saigon]]. [[Viet Cong]] forces are suspected of placing a bomb on the ship.
*  1964   &amp;ndash; [[First ascent]] of [[Shishapangma]] the fourteenth highest [[mountain]] in the world and the lowest of the [[Eight-thousander]]s.
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; The [[Great Britain|British]] [[ocean liner]] [[RMS Queen Elizabeth 2|''Queen Elizabeth 2'']] departs on her maiden voyage to [[New York City]].
*[[1972]] &amp;ndash; In the early morning hours a fire broke out at the [[Sunshine mine]] located between Kellogg and Wallace, ID, killing 91 workers.
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; [[Falklands War]]: The British [[nuclear submarine]] [[HMS Conqueror (S48)|HMS ''Conqueror'']] sinks the [[Argentina|Argentine]] cruiser [[ARA General Belgrano|ARA ''General Belgrano'']].
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[Hungary]] begins [[Removal of Hungary's border fence|dismantling its border fence]] with [[Austria]], which allows a number of [[East Germany|East Germans]] to defect.
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; A bus [[Poland bus disaster of 1994|crashes]] in [[Gdańsk|Gdańsk, Poland]] killing 32 people.
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; During the [[Croatian War of Independence]], [[Serb]] forces [[Zagreb rocket attack|fire cluster bombs]] at [[Zagreb]], killing 7 and wounding over 175 civilians.
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; The [[European Central Bank]] is founded in [[Brussels]] in order to define and execute the [[European Union]]'s monetary policy.
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Panamanian election, 1999]]: [[Mireya Moscoso]] becomes the first woman to be elected [[List of Heads of State of Panama|President]] of [[Panama]].
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; [[President of the United States|President]] [[Bill Clinton]] announces that accurate [[Global Positioning System|GPS]] access would no longer be restricted to the [[United States Armed Forces|United States military]].
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Yelwa massacre]] of more than 630 [[nomad]] [[Muslims]] by [[Christians]] in [[Nigeria]].
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[Cyclone Nargis]] makes landfall in [[Burma]] killing over 138,000 people and leaving millions of people homeless.
*  2008   &amp;ndash; [[Chaitén (volcano)|Chaitén Volcano]] begins erupting in [[Chile]], forcing the evacuation of more than 4,500 people.
*[[2011]] &amp;ndash; [[Osama bin Laden]], the suspected mastermind behind the [[September 11 attacks]] and the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]]'s most wanted man is [[Death of Osama bin Laden|killed]] by the [[Navy SEALs|United States special forces]] in [[Abbottabad]], [[Pakistan]].
*  2011   &amp;ndash; An [[2011 E. coli O104:H4 outbreak|E. coli outbreak]] strikes Europe, mostly in Germany, leaving more than 30 people dead and many others sick from the [[bacteria]] outbreak.
*[[2012]] &amp;ndash; A [[pastel]] version of ''[[The Scream]]'', by [[Norway|Norwegian]] painter [[Edvard Munch]], sells for $120 million in a [[New York City]] auction, setting a new world record for an auctioned work of art.

