*[[1880]] &amp;ndash; [[Eberhard Anheuser]], German soap and candle maker, founder of the [[Anheuser-Busch]] Company (b. 1805)
*[[1885]] &amp;ndash; [[Terézia Zakoucs]], Hungarian Slovene author (b. 1817)
*[[1927]] &amp;ndash; [[Ernest Starling]], British physiologist (b. 1866)
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Martin Bormann]], German [[Nazi]] official (b. 1900)
*  1945   &amp;ndash; [[Joe Corbett]], American baseball player (b. 1875)
*  1945   &amp;ndash; [[Ludwig Stumpfegger]], German [[SS]] doctor (b. 1910)
*[[1947]] &amp;ndash; [[Dorothea Binz]], German [[SS]] supervisor (b. 1920)
*[[1953]] &amp;ndash; [[Wallace Bryant (archer)|Wallace Bryant]], American archer (b. 1863)
*[[1957]] &amp;ndash; [[Joseph McCarthy]], American politician (b. 1908)
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[Caryl Chessman]], American convicted robber and rapist (b. 1921)
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Nancy Astor, Viscountess Astor]], American-English politician (first woman to take her seat in the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|British House of Commons]]) (b. 1879)
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; [[Franz von Papen]], German politician, [[Chancellor of Germany (German Reich)|Chancellor of Germany]] (b. 1879)
*[[1972]] &amp;ndash; [[J. Edgar Hoover]], American 1st [[director of the Federal Bureau of Investigation]] (b. 1895)
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[James O. Richardson]], American admiral (b. 1878)
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; [[Giulio Natta]], Italian chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1903)
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; [[Clarrie Grimmett]], Australian cricketer (b. 1891)
*  1980   &amp;ndash; [[George Pal]], Hungarian director (b. 1908)
*[[1983]] &amp;ndash; [[Norm Van Brocklin]], American football player (b. 1926)
*[[1984]] &amp;ndash; [[Jack Barry (television)|Jack Barry]], television producer and host (b. 1918)
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; [[Attilio Bettega]], Italian race car driver (b. 1951)
*  1985   &amp;ndash; [[Larry Clinton]], American trumpeter and bandleader (b. 1909)
*[[1986]] &amp;ndash; [[Sergio Cresto]], American race car driver (b. 1956)
*  1986   &amp;ndash; [[Henri Toivonen]], Finnish race car driver (b. 1956)
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[Veniamin Kaverin]], Russian writer (b. 1902)
*  1989   &amp;ndash; [[Giuseppe Siri]], Italian cardinal (b. 1906)
